<subSubSection pageId="85" pageNumber="2315" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="85.[160,1155,1390,1554]" pageId="85" pageNumber="2315">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,282,1390,1415]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="2315">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
this species is separated from other in the group by the following combined characters: males pronotum with pair of weak knobs on the anterior portion of disc; elytral striae and punctures deeply impressed; males paramera with a longitudinal carina inserted on the longitudinal excavation (
<figureCitation box="[632,743,1495,1519]" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="50.[160,225,1682,1705]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1634]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[163,1153,142,1650]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figure 35. D. blancoi: (a) male dorsal habitus; (b) paramera dorsal view; (c) paramera ventral view; (d) paramera lateral view; (e) detail of the carena found on the middle of paramera longitudinal excavation. D. candangoi: (f) male dorsal habitus; (g) paramera dorsal view; (h) paramera ventral view; (i) paramera lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3665585/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="2315">Figure 35</figureCitation>
(e)). Very similar to many species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Felsche" authorityYear="1901" box="[204,344,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pinotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="2315" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadraticeps">
<emphasis box="[204,344,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="2315">quadraticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groupı being differentiated basically by males genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
